# The everyday commands

Module-03 verbs, scoped to the **whole project**.

| Command | Does |
|---|---|
| `up [-d]` | create + start all (`-d` detached) |
| `up -d --build` | rebuild `build:` images first |
| `down [-v]` | stop + remove (+ volumes) |
| `ps` / `logs [-f]` | state / tail logs |
| `exec svc sh` | shell into a **running** service |
| `run --rm svc cmd` | **new** one-off container (migrations) |
| `config` | print resolved YAML |

## Two to burn in

- **`exec` vs `run`** — `exec` = inside the running container; `run` = a fresh, separate one for a task. Inspect vs. do.
- **`config` is your debugger** — prints the final YAML after `.env` + overrides. See what Compose *thinks* you asked for.
